class LFUCache {
    constructor(capacity) {
        this.capacity = capacity;
        this.minFreq = 0;
        this.keyValue = new Map();
        this.keyFreq = new Map();
        this.freqList = new Map();
        this.freqList.set(1, new Set());
    }

    get(key) {
        if (!this.keyValue.has(key)) return -1;
        let count = this.keyFreq.get(key);
        this.keyFreq.set(key, count + 1);
        this.freqList.get(count).delete(key);

        if (count === this.minFreq && this.freqList.get(count).size === 0) this.minFreq++;

        if (!this.freqList.has(count + 1)) this.freqList.set(count + 1, new Set());
        this.freqList.get(count + 1).add(key);

        return this.keyValue.get(key);
    }

    put(key, value) {
        if (this.capacity <= 0) return;
        if (this.keyValue.has(key)) {
            this.keyValue.set(key, value);
            this.get(key);
            return;
        }
        if (this.keyValue.size >= this.capacity) {
            const evict = this.freqList.get(this.minFreq).values().next().value;
            this.freqList.get(this.minFreq).delete(evict);
            this.keyValue.delete(evict);
        }
        this.keyValue.set(key, value);
        this.keyFreq.set(key, 1);
        this.minFreq = 1;
        this.freqList.get(1).add(key);
    }
}
```


    The implemented LFUCache is a combined data structure using a hash map and linked lists. We maintain 3 key-value mappings: the first is the cache `keyValue` which stores `<key, value>` pairs; the second is `keyFreq`, which keeps track of each key's frequency; the last is `freqList` which keeps the mapping of frequency to a list/set of keys that are at that frequency.

Both get() and put() operations take constant O(1) average time complexity:

1. get():
  - With the help of hashmaps, retrieve the value for the key in constant time.
  - Increment the key’s frequency in `keyFreq` by 1.
  - Update the corresponding list/set of the `freqList`.
  - Update the minFreq if necessary.

2. put():
  - Check if the key is already present in the cache. If it is, update the value, and perform get() operation, thus maintaining frequency count.
  - If the key is not present, add the key-value pair and set its frequency to 1.
  - Evict the LFU (least frequently used) key if necessary, by removing a key from the list/set of `freqList[minFreq]`.

Note that in Java and JavaScript, we use LinkedHashSet / Set, while in Python we use list within the `freqList`. This is due to language-specific details.

